HEADWORD: Zinkenite
<hw>Zink"en*ite</hw> <pr>(-⟦eit⟧n*⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[From <etsep>Zinken</etsep>, director at one time of the Hanoverian
mines.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A steel-gray metallic mineral, a
sulphide of antimony and lead.</def>⟦br⟧
